If a class has even ONE abstract method → class must be abstract
Child must implement ALL abstract methods
Abstract class can have 0 abstract methods
Can Abstract Classes Have Constructors?
Can Abstract Methods Be Static?

Key Takeaways (Memorize This)
•	Abstract classes cannot be instantiated
•	Used for IS-A relationship
•	Can contain:
o	Fields
o	Constructors
o	Abstract + concrete methods
•	Child classes must implement abstract methods
•	Perfect for partial abstraction


They meant to represent a “general idea”?
 Yes — exactly.
Examples:
•	Animal
•	Vehicle
•	Employee
•	PaymentMethod
•	NotificationService
These are categories, not real instances.
